name: Bytenode Compiled JavaScript
summary: A JSC file is a JavaScript ( .JS ) file that has been compiled by the bytenode package for Node.js. It contains JavaScript source code that has been translated from plain text to bytecode . Compiling a JS file to a JSC file allows developers to obscure the source code the JS file contains (preventing others from copying or stealing it).
